LINE.Text: Worst U.S. drought in 50 years increases
The scorching drought in the Midwest has ravaged fields and driven up the price of soybeans, wheat and corn, with domino effects on the cost of
meat and other products. Economists fear the drought could impact global food prices since the United States is a maior agricultural exporter
Sources: USDA: NOM: U.S. Drought Monitor. Graphic News
